article.headline: N. Carolina A&amp,T 65, Delaware St. 54
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. -- Robert Johnson shot 6-for-6 from the field and scored 17 points to lead North Carolina A&T to a 65-54 win over Delaware State on Saturday. Dwane Joshua added 16 points for the Aggies (8-15, 4-5 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference), while Thomas Coleman chipped in with 10 points and 11 rebounds. Marcus Neal finished with 16 points on 6 of 17 shooting for the Hornets (11-9, 6-3), and Marques Oliver grabbed 10 rebounds. Delaware State saw a three-game winning streak snapped with the loss. North Carolina A&T shot 56.1 percent from the field (23-for-41), including 57.1 percent from 3-point range (8-for-14). Delaware State shot 36.5 percent from the field (23-for-63) and shot 21.4 percent from beyond the arc (6-for-28). The Aggies outrebounded Delaware State 37-31.
